	Hi-tech wedding    
	 Jerusalem, July 10 (Reuters): Guests at an Israeli wedding hall can now insert a credit card into a machine at its entrance, tap in a sum and leave a gift for the bride and groom.      
	Its new in Israel and the world, Aya Alon Kaufman of the Gan Oranim hall in Tel Aviv said. Its very convenient... guests can give a gift even if they forget their chequebooks. She said couples pay 500 shekels ($155) to rent the device, which resembles an automated teller machine.                                                                                                                                                                      
